  * **Near real-time interactive machining, probably per \#1 (below)**  
    * Ted Hall, some thoughts:   (Neil made me do it …)  
    * 1\. (FabMo-Art thing) Near real-time, interactive, robotic 3D drawing, engraving, and carving. Leveraging the power and precision of the head of a robotic tool to express art. Exploring how dynamic motion planning approximates the direct control of an artist’s tool, limited only by the small amount of time needed to filter, smooth, adjust, or limit the projected action.  
        \- To what degree can we accommodate a small lag in motion; how does this relate to robotic surgery?  
        \- In what ways might some sort of feedback or A-R guidance facilitate?   
    * 2\. (My art interest, continuation from earlier Haystack participation) Hybrid, hand-inked, 3d, carved waterscapes, as a form of printmaking on topographic surfaces where CNC carving provides one component of the “print”. [https://handibot.com/blog/2015/08/doing-art-with-handibot/](https://handibot.com/blog/2015/08/doing-art-with-handibot/)  
    * Use of any ShopBot (will bring new electronics)
